functions.name: delegate
functions.desc:
Ask a capable helper for help looking up a piece of information or performing an action.
Do not simply repeat what the user said as instructions.
You should use this to break up complex user queries into multiple simpler steps.
NOTE: Helpers cannot see previous parts of your conversation.

instructions.description: Detailed instructions on what your helper should do to help you.

msg.content: What were box office values of the Star Wars films in the prequel and sequel trilogies?
What were box office values of the Star Wars films in the prequel and sequel trilogies?

Here are the lifetime US box office totals for the Star Wars films in the prequel and sequel trilogies:

- *Star Wars: Episode I – The Phantom Menace* (1999): $431,088,301
- *Star Wars: Episode II – Attack of the Clones* (2002): $302,191,252
- *Star Wars: Episode III – Revenge of the Sith* (2005): $380,270,577
- *Star Wars: Episode VII – The Force Awakens* (2015): $936,662,225
- *Star Wars: Episode VIII – The Last Jedi* (2017): $620,181,382
- *Star Wars: Episode IX – The Rise of Skywalker* (2019): $515,256,839

*Star Wars: Episode V – The Empire Strikes Back* (1980) and *Star Wars: Episode VI – Return of the Jedi* (1983) also grossed $290,475,067 and $309,306,177 respectively, during their original release and subsequent re-releases.
